    "As discussed by Tan (2018), the level of potential stimuli one can experience from a film far surpasses the complexity of audience attention.",
    "Thus, GLAMOUR could be extended to include other processes involved in automated shot composition, such as kernalized filter control (KCF), presented by Henriques et al. (2014) and used for actor detection and framing in automated aerial content acquisition (discussed in Sect. 3.4.1).",
    "Additionally useful, cinematic motion style transfer in Wang et al. (2023) uses 3-D representations generated from real images and matched to a shot sequence from a scene in a given movie.",
    "This could be paired with attention optimization to improve upon selected idiomatic shot to transfer, from which we could derive more meaningful camera poses and motions.",
    "A semi-automated method introduced by Yu et al. (2022) was designed to handle object staging, automated camera positioning and shot composition, from an annotated script."
